    <h1>�Œ™ Evening Market Update: Meme Coins Give Back Gains as BTC Dips 4.6%</h1>
    <div class="meta">
        <strong>Published:</strong> June 2, 2026 ” 9:00 PM ICT | <strong>Category:</strong> Market Analysis / Flash Update | <strong>Reading Time:</strong> 4 min
    </div>

    <div class="highlight-box">
        <strong>TL;DR:</strong> This morning's meme coin rally has faded as Bitcoin dropped 4.6% to $68,112. DOGE, BONK, and PEPE each fell 2-2.5% from intraday highs. However, $DKING held remarkably well at just -1% ” the strongest relative performance among major meme coins this evening. Here's what happened and how to position for the overnight session.
    </div>

    <h2>What Happened: The Rally That Peaked Too Fast</h2>
    <p>Earlier today, the meme coin market surged across the board ” BONK hit +15.1%, DOGE jumped +12.4%, and $DKING climbed +8.2%. The summer rally narrative was in full swing, and sentiment was overwhelmingly bullish.</p>
    <p>But by the evening session (Asia/Pacific time zone), a sharp Bitcoin pullback changed the game. BTC dropped from intraday highs above $71,000 to $68,112 ” a -4.6% move that triggered a broad crypto market sell-off. Meme coins, which had run hard during the morning, were the most affected.</p>

    <div class="warning-box">
        <strong>⚠ Key Observation:</strong> The morning rally was classic "front-run" behavior ” traders anticipated the summer momentum and bought aggressively, only to take profits when BTC showed weakness. This doesn't mean the rally is over ” but it does mean we're seeing normal profit-taking in an uptrend.
    </div>

