    <h2>$DKING Shows Relative Strength ” Here's Why</h2>
    <p>The standout data point this evening is $DKING's relative resilience. While every other major meme coin dropped 2-2.5%, $DKING only fell 0.99%. In a session where even Bitcoin shed 4.6%, this is a strong signal.</p>

    <h3>Why $DKING Held Better Than Peers:</h3>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Lower retail leverage.</strong> Unlike DOGE and BONK, which see heavy futures and perpetuals trading, $DKING trades primarily on spot DEX markets. This means less forced liquidations during BTC drawdowns.</li>
        <li><strong>Educational content moat.</strong> The DogeKing.us platform (280+ guides) drives consistent organic traffic that isn't correlated with short-term price action. New readers discover $DKING through search, not price pumps.</li>
        <li><strong>Deflationary buffer.</strong> $DKING's 1% burn mechanism continues to reduce supply regardless of price direction. Every transaction during the morning rally actually made the token scarcer, creating a natural support floor.</li>
        <li><strong>Lower volatility profile.</strong> $DKING has historically shown lower daily volatility than DOGE or BONK, which means less dramatic pullbacks during market-wide corrections.</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="info-box">
        <strong>�œŠ Volume Data:</strong> Despite the pullback, $DKING recorded $66,901 in 24-hour volume ” solid for a micro-cap meme coin. This suggests genuine trading activity rather than bot-driven wash trading.
    </div>

